pesticide.PPE: Long-sleeved shirt and long pants; Shoes plus socks.

Safety_Information.general_Info: Harmful if swallowed. Prolonged or frequently repeated skin contact may cause allergic reaction in some individuals.
Safety_Information.if_Swallowed: Call a poison control center or doctor immediately for treatment advice. Have person sip a glass of water if able to swallow. Do not induce vomiting unless told by a poison control center or doctor. Do not give anything by mouth to an unconscious person.
Safety_Information.physician_Note: For emergency medical treatment, contact Rocky Mountain Poison and Drug Safety at 1-866-673-6671. For 24-hour chemical emergency (spill, leaks, fire, exposure or accident) call CHEMTREC at 1-800-424-9300 or +1-703-527-3887.
